title: Major collision on southbound Interstate 5 closes all lanes of traffic, kills two
text:
February 18, 2017 8:57 AM Major collision on southbound Interstate 5 closes all lanes of traffic, kills two A collision on southbound Interstate 5 shut down all lanes of traffic Saturday morning, the Sacramento Fire Department said. Sacramento Fire Department i 
By Nashelly Chavez 
A major collision closed all southbound lanes of Interstate 5 near the J Street exit Saturday morning. 
BOOKMARK: See current Sacramento traffic 
The Sacramento Fire Department confirmed two fatalities and transported one person to the hospital with critical injuries, according to a department tweet sent out just before 8:30 a.m. 
The fire department initially reported the multi-vehicle collision 8:07 a.m. Traffic on the highway is being rerouted as crews continue to work at the scene. Drivers are urged to find alternative routes. 
Sacramento Fire Department spokesman Chris Harvey said the person taken to the hospital was a truck driver who was involved in the collision. Southbound lanes were still closed by 9:10 a.m., he said. Photos from Southbound I-5 incident show fire crews extricating patient from truck. Man was transported to hospital with severe injuries. pic.twitter.com/GqQqsCcHMm — Sacramento Fire (@SacFirePIO) February 18, 2017
